      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Preserve wrapper-backed gateway services during doctor repairs",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve existing gateway wrappers when doctor/update rebuilds service install plans\n- treat wrapper-driven gateway service commands as valid during service audit\n- refuse destructive direct-exec fallback when an inferred legacy wrapper is missing\n\n## Why\n`openclaw update --yes` can run doctor repair after updating. For legacy macOS LaunchAgents whose `ProgramArguments` contain only an opaque wrapper script, audit previously flagged the service as missing the `gateway` subcommand. Doctor repair then rebuilt the LaunchAgent without the wrapper, dropping Keychain/env secret loading and causing gateway startup to fail on unresolved SecretRefs such as `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN`.\n\n## Tests\n- wrapper inference and preservation from existing service argv/env\n- wrapper-driven service audit behavior\n- missing inferred wrapper refusal path\n- integration regression for a wrapper-only LaunchAgent matching the observed update failure",
